HEADWORD: Short-winded
<hw>Short"-wind`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Affected with
shortness of breath; having a quick, difficult respiration, as dyspnoic
and asthmatic persons.</def> <rj><au>May.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

